Installation de Apache
======================

pacman -S apache php php-apache mariadb

## Test config
```
apachectl configtest
apachectl -t
```

## List all running virtual host
```
apache2ctl -S
```

## Debian / Ubuntu specific configuration file
The “master” configuration file for Apache is located in the apache2.conf file and the httpd.conf file contains user-specific configuration 

## Configuration directory
Configuration files are stored in the conf.d/ directory
ex: /etc/apache2/conf.d/vhosts.conf